Package org.jdbi.v3.mapper

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ColumnMapper<T>
    Maps result set columns to objects.
    ColumnMapperFactory
    Factory interface used to produce column mappers.
    RowMapper<T>
    Used with a Query.map(RowMapper) call to specify what to do with each row of a result set
    RowMapperFactory
    Factory interface used to produce row mappers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BeanMapper<T>
    A row mapper which maps the fields in a statement into a JavaBean.
    BeanMapperFactory  
    BuiltInMapperFactory
    Column mapper factory which knows how to map JDBC-recognized types, along with some other well-known types from the JDK.
    ConstructorMapper<T>
    A row mapper which maps the fields in a result set into a constructor.
    DefaultMapper  
    EnumByNameMapperFactory
    Produces enum column mappers, which map enums from varchar columns using Enum.valueOf(Class, String).
    EnumByOrdinalMapperFactory
    Produces enum column mappers, which map enums from numeric columns according to ordinal value.
    EnumMapper<E extends Enum<E>>  
    FieldMapper<T>
    A row mapper which maps the fields in a statement into an object.
    InferredColumnMapperFactory
    A generic ColumnMapperFactory that reflectively inspects a ColumnMapper<T> and maps only to columns of type T.
    InferredRowMapperFactory
    A generic RowMapperFactory that reflectively inspects a RowMapper<T> and maps only to columns of type T.
